","id":"70edac97","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.007411,"end_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.938019+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.930608+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["**Optuna** is a tool used to **automatically find the best hyperparameters** for machine learning models.\n","### Simple Idea\n","Instead of manually trying different settings, Optuna:\n","- Tries many combinations\n","- Learns from past trials\n","- Finds the best settings faster\n","\n","### Key Features\n","- **Automatic tuning** of hyperparameters  \n","- **Efficient search** (tries smart combinations)  \n","- **Pruning** → stops bad trials early to save time  \n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"70771918","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.006598,"end_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.951924+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.945326+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["# Optuna Objective Function\n","\n","**Definition:**  \n","The **objective function** in Optuna is the function that evaluates a set of hyperparameters and returns a performance score. Optuna uses this score to find the best hyperparameters.\n","\n","## Key Points\n","\n","- **Purpose:** Tell Optuna how good a model is for given hyperparameters.  \n","- **Returns:** A single value (e.g., RMSE, R²) to **minimize** or **maximize**.  \n","- **Structure:**\n","  1. Suggest hyperparameters using `trial.suggest_*`\n","  2. Train your model with these hyperparameters\n","  3. Evaluate the model on validation data\n","  4. Return the performance metric\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":19,"id":"ba5530cb","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.96717Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.966812Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.972734Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.971818Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.015983,"end_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.974631+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.958648+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["def objective(trial):\n","\n","    #hyperparameter\n","    params = {\n","         \"max_depth\" : trial.suggest_int('max_depth', 1, 10),\n","    \"min_samples_split\" : trial.suggest_int('min_samples_split', 2, 10),\n","    \"min_samples_leaf\" : trial.suggest_int('min_samples_leaf', 1, 5)}\n","\n","    #model\n","    model =  DecisionTreeRegressor(**params, random_state=42)\n","\n","    # cross-validation\n","    kf=KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)\n","    scores=cross_val_score(model1, X_train, y_train, cv=kf, scoring='r2')\n","\n","    return np.mean(scores)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"339aa9d3","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.006808,"end_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.98836+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.981552+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["# Optuna Trial\n","\n","**Definition:**  \n","A **Trial** in Optuna represents a **single run of the objective function** with a specific set of hyperparameters. Each trial evaluates the model and returns a score.\n","\n","## Key Points\n","\n","- **Purpose:** Track **one combination of hyperparameters** and its performance.\n","- **Hyperparameter suggestions:** Use `trial.suggest_*` methods:\n","  ```python\n","  learning_rate = trial.suggest_float(\"learning_rate\", 0.01, 0.2)\n","  max_depth = trial.suggest_int(\"max_depth\", 2, 6)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"2b83b425","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.006587,"end_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:40.001776+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:39.995189+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["# Optuna Study\n","\n","**Definition:**  \n","A **Study** in Optuna is the **object that manages the optimization process**. It keeps track of all trials, hyperparameters tested, and their evaluation results.\n","\n","## Key Points\n","\n","- **Purpose:** Coordinate the search for the best hyperparameters.  \n","- **Contains:**  \n","  - All trials and their results  \n","  - Best hyperparameters found  \n","  - Optimization direction (`minimize` or `maximize`)  "]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":20,"id":"583b8bbe","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-08T04:09:40.016852Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-08T04:09:40.016553Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-08T04:09:51.428879Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-08T04:09:51.427826Z"},"papermill":{"duration":11.422318,"end_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:51.430908+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-08T04:09:40.00859+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","output_type":"stream","text":["[I 2026-04-08 04:09:40,018] A new study created in memory with name: no-name-c1639015-7a1c-43b0-b135-61388adf4f04\n","[I 2026-04-08 04:09:40,244] Trial 0 finished with value: 0.999480644388971 and parameters: {'max_depth': 1, 'min_samples_split': 7, 'min_samples_leaf': 4}. Best is trial 0 with value: 0.999480644388971.\n","[I 2026-04-08 04:09:40,473] Trial 1 finished with value: 0.999480644388971 and parameters: {'max_depth': 3, 'min_samples_split': 9, 'min_samples_leaf': 2}. Best is trial 0 with value: 0.999480644388971.\n","[I 2026-04-08 04:09:40,695] Trial 2 finished with value: 0.999480644388971 and parameters: {'max_depth': 9, 'min_samples_split': 10, 'min_samples_leaf': 1}. Best is trial 0 with value: 0.999480644388971.\n","[I 2026-04-08 04:09:40,916] Trial 3 finished with value: 0.999480644388971 and parameters: {'max_depth': 4, 'min_samples_split': 4, 'min_samples_leaf': 5}. Best is trial 0 with value: 0.999480644388971.\n","[I 2026-04-08 04:09:41,140] Trial 4 finished with value: 0.999480644388971 and parameters: {'max_depth': 4, 'min_samples_split': 8, 'min_samples_leaf': 4}. Best is trial 0 with value: 0.999480644388971.\n","[I 2026-04-08 04:09:41,362] Trial 5 finished with value: 0.999480644388971 and parameters: {'max_depth': 7, 'min_samples_split': 5, 'min_samples_leaf': 5}. 